## Remarks  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-492">O <xref:System.Xml.XmlValidatingReader> classe está obsoleta no [!INCLUDE[dnprdnext](~/includes/dnprdnext-md.md)].</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-492">The <xref:System.Xml.XmlValidatingReader> class is obsolete in [!INCLUDE[dnprdnext](~/includes/dnprdnext-md.md)].</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-493">Você pode criar um Validando <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> instância usando o <xref:System.Xml.XmlReaderSettings> classe e o <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Create%2A> método.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-493">You can create a validating <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> instance by using the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReaderSettings> class and the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Create%2A> method.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-494">Para obter mais informações, consulte a seção de Comentários da página de referência <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-494">For more information, see the Remarks section of the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> reference page.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-495">Use este método depois de chamar <xref:System.Xml.XmlValidatingReader.MoveToAttribute%2A> para ler os nós de referência de texto ou uma entidade que compõem o valor do atributo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-495">Use this method after calling <xref:System.Xml.XmlValidatingReader.MoveToAttribute%2A> to read through the text or entity reference nodes that make up the attribute value.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-496">O <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Depth%2A> de nós de valor do atributo é um mais a profundidade do nó de atributo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-496">The <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Depth%2A> of the attribute value nodes is one plus the depth of the attribute node.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-497">O `Depth` incrementa e decrementa por um quando a etapa dentro e fora de referências a entidades geral.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-497">The `Depth` increments and decrements by one when you step into and out of general entity references.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-498">Por exemplo, suponha que você tem o seguinte XML: `<test name="a &b; c"/>`</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-498">For example, suppose you have the following XML: `<test name="a &b; c"/>`</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-499">em que a entidade `b` é definido no document type definition (DTD) da seguinte maneira: `<!ENTITY b "123">`</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-499">where the entity `b` is defined in the document type definition (DTD) as follows: `<!ENTITY b "123">`</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="9b9b0-500">Se <xref:System.Xml.XmlValidatingReader.EntityHandling%2A> é definido como `ExpandCharEntities`, o código c# a seguir retorna o valor do atributo como dois nós de texto e o nó de referência de uma entidade:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="9b9b0-500">If <xref:System.Xml.XmlValidatingReader.EntityHandling%2A> is set to `ExpandCharEntities`, the following C# code returns the attribute value as two text nodes and one entity reference node:</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
reader.MoveToAttribute("name");  
  while (reader.ReadAttributeValue())  
  {  
  if (reader.NodeType == XmlNodeType.Text)  
  {  
  // at this point reader.Value == "a " or " c"  
  }  
  else if (reader.NodeType == XmlNodeType.EntityReference)  
  {  
  // at this point reader.Name == "b"  
  reader.ResolveEntity();  
  while (reader.ReadAttributeValue() &&  
  reader.NodeType != XmlNodeType.EndEntity)  
  {  
  // reader.Value == "123"  
  }  
  }  
    }  
```  
  
   
  
